r three months and enlarged posterior cervical lymph nodes.","dimension":10,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.14464,0.24536,0.16891,0.081824,0.065723,0.072148,0.048889,0.058933,0.035857,0.030646,0.025412,0.021658],"unified_progress":[0.11576,0.16529,0.13377,0.09424,0.08558,0.08848,0.067623,0.080846,0.053875,0.046068,0.038424,0.03005]},{"section":4,"text":"The lab results show leukopenia and low C4 complement levels.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.085413,0.14336,0.14304,0.12089,0.098417,0.085878,0.076567,0.067727,0.057189,0.048222,0.041733,0.031562],"unified_progress":[0.072136,0.11758,0.11432,0.10943,0.11091,0.097993,0.08966,0.078172,0.068385,0.057528,0.04897,0.03491]},{"section":5,"text":"Hmm, Sj\u00f6gren's can sometimes lead to other issues.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.073436,0.10951,0.11458,0.11279,0.10296,0.090466,0.083639,0.075867,0.066147,0.066819,0.053572,0.050214],"unified_progress":[0.089769,0.084151,0.090338,0.10043,0.096712,0.094292,0.089468,0.087037,0.078635,0.076838,0.06307,0.049263]},{"section":6,"text":"The parotid swelling makes me think of salivary gland involvement, which is common, but usually in Sj\u00f6gren's it's bilateral and chronic.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.046549,0.089894,0.10301,0.10744,0.1045,0.098688,0.093427,0.085113,0.078256,0.075403,0.061705,0.056011],"unified_progress":[0.044243,0.072909,0.091497,0.1009,0.10181,0.10287,0.09815,0.093575,0.088671,0.083284,0.067605,0.05448]},{"section":7,"text":"However, the lymphadenopathy and the new lab abnormalities might point to something else.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.040359,0.085891,0.10333,0.10658,0.10102,0.093514,0.090859,0.085406,0.081311,0.082075,0.068825,0.060835],"unified_progress":[0.037945,0.071293,0.084727,0.096207,0.099013,0.096857,0.098014,0.095627,0.092975,0.092932,0.076431,0.05798]},{"section":8,"text":"Leukopenia and low complement levels (like C4) often suggest active inflammation or another autoimmune process.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.041564,0.084941,0.099652,0.10307,0.1007,0.095697,0.095239,0.089103,0.083125,0.078423,0.070413,0.058068],"unified_progress":[0.039845,0.0741,0.089944,0.095302,0.10189,0.099471,0.10027,0.093924,0.089847,0.08449,0.074361,0.056558]},{"section":9,"text":"Wait, could this be a lymphoma?","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.045375,0.083111,0.095978,0.10044,0.099099,0.093236,0.091731,0.088958,0.08404,0.08418,0.071641,0.062213],"unified_progress":[0.054285,0.073748,0.086583,0.099216,0.098666,0.096324,0.096912,0.094126,0.088857,0.085968,0.071445,0.053869]},{"section":10,"text":"I remember that patients with Sj\u00f6gren's have an increased risk of developing non-Hodgkin's lymphoma, especially B-cell types.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03616,0.072267,0.08502,0.095403,0.10212,0.10471,0.10151,0.095342,0.086859,0.085509,0.071372,0.063736],"unified_progress":[0.051562,0.077455,0.088276,0.091859,0.096003,0.10346,0.097622,0.096362,0.088905,0.082491,0.069234,0.056775]},{"section":11,"text":"The parotid swelling might be due to lymphoma involvement, and the lymph nodes are enlarged.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031799,0.070888,0.083911,0.092661,0.096125,0.099353,0.10041,0.094643,0.10038,0.084986,0.07696,0.067889],"unified_progress":[0.037928,0.064964,0.081867,0.092388,0.10003,0.10208,0.099068,0.096,0.099968,0.086316,0.076949,0.062444]},{"section":12,"text":"The low C4 might indicate an immune complex disease, but in the context of Sj\u00f6gren's and lymphadenopathy, lymphoma is a big concern.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032454,0.068331,0.082726,0.090812,0.094578,0.095555,0.097966,0.095133,0.092131,0.092056,0.082549,0.07571],"unified_progress":[0.03944,0.061705,0.074039,0.083027,0.090716,0.09421,0.097338,0.097854,0.09782,0.097484,0.090219,0.076149]},{"section":13,"text":"Other possibilities?","dimension":12,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029931,0.068522,0.089604,0.096642,0.097505,0.093682,0.093745,0.092398,0.090751,0.092889,0.081029,0.073301],"unified_progress":[0.032312,0.067097,0.081015,0.094731,0.095649,0.09471,0.097784,0.096502,0.094284,0.098077,0.083344,0.064495]},{"section":14,"text":"Maybe a secondary Sj\u00f6gren's complication like vasculitis, but vasculitis would more likely present with different symptoms like rash or organ involvement.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.023456,0.056797,0.072155,0.083913,0.09352,0.098954,0.10554,0.10517,0.1015,0.099147,0.090092,0.069755],"unified_progress":[0.027916,0.054322,0.071183,0.080507,0.092581,0.099865,0.10215,0.10657,0.10553,0.10644,0.089333,0.063611]},{"section":15,"text":"The combination of parotid swelling, lymphadenopathy, leukopenia, and low complement...","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.024688,0.055258,0.067777,0.077101,0.086114,0.093527,0.099152,0.10043,0.10363,0.10148,0.10202,0.088813],"unified_progress":[0.032873,0.055365,0.067982,0.077688,0.088119,0.097923,0.099317,0.10222,0.10506,0.10316,0.095934,0.074362]},{"section":16,"text":"Lymphoma seems to fit better.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.027732,0.060878,0.077254,0.0845,0.08689,0.08625,0.090034,0.090894,0.092674,0.098528,0.094568,0.1098],"unified_progress":[0.028935,0.051196,0.063486,0.074856,0.08005,0.086682,0.09045,0.096509,0.10001,0.10518,0.10938,0.11327]},{"section":17,"text":"Also, the duration of three months isn't too short for lymphoma to develop.","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036354,0.071594,0.081321,0.0864,0.089237,0.091786,0.093282,0.094183,0.093302,0.094264,0.087435,0.080841],"unified_progress":[0.047974,0.069999,0.075453,0.081292,0.085917,0.088912,0.091951,0.095922,0.095969,0.098596,0.090846,0.07717]},{"section":18,"text":"Another angle: maybe a parotid gland infection?","dimension":0,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.025808,0.059697,0.075944,0.085884,0.094268,0.097529,0.10065,0.10201,0.10375,0.098098,0.088574,0.067791],"unified_progress":[0.033742,0.068575,0.086498,0.099799,0.1004,0.098991,0.10216,0.098683,0.096658,0.089401,0.073016,0.052073]},{"section":19,"text":"But she's had it for three months, which is more chronic.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030011,0.064377,0.07417,0.080824,0.088365,0.095952,0.099727,0.10261,0.1012,0.099219,0.091916,0.071628],"unified_progress":[0.049112,0.07892,0.082776,0.084949,0.09208,0.092801,0.094029,0.099423,0.095581,0.094639,0.079608,0.056083]},{"section":20,"text":"Infections usually resolve quicker unless chronic, but the lab results don't point to ongoing infection.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.018719,0.04899,0.065376,0.077257,0.086507,0.094114,0.10595,0.10969,0.11,0.10857,0.10258,0.072255],"unified_progress":[0.029714,0.055447,0.070036,0.078651,0.092393,0.095086,0.10139,0.10824,0.1082,0.11344,0.09205,0.055348]},{"section":21,"text":"The low complement could be part of the autoimmune process, but in Sj\u00f6gren's, complement levels aren't typically low unless there's another issue.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.027184,0.059536,0.07324,0.083183,0.091062,0.096468,0.1022,0.10232,0.099949,0.097524,0.09157,0.075761],"unified_progress":[0.042653,0.062595,0.074416,0.081964,0.090519,0.09583,0.097756,0.1,0.099296,0.097869,0.089411,0.067688]},{"section":22,"text":"So putting it all together: primary Sj\u00f6gren's patient with new parotid swelling, lymphadenopathy, leukopenia, low C4.","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.027003,0.054026,0.064945,0.073741,0.082658,0.089784,0.095561,0.097673,0.10241,0.10375,0.10686,0.10159],"